#: ../../L/loop-through.rst:5
msgid "loop through"
msgstr "loop through"

#: ../../L/loop-through.rst:7
msgid "vt\\."
msgstr "他動詞"

#: ../../L/loop-through.rst:9
msgid ""
"To process each element of a list of things. \"Hold on, I've got to loop "
"through my paper mail.\" Derives from the computer-language notion of an "
"iterative loop; compare cdr down (under :ref:`cdr`\\), which is less common "
"among C and Unix programmers. ITS hackers used to say IRP over after an "
"obscure pseudo-op in the MIDAS PDP-10 assembler (the same IRP op can "
"nowadays be found in Microsoft's assembler)."
msgstr ""
"ものごとのリストの各要素を処理すること。「待ってくれ、紙のメールをloop "
"throughしないといけない。」コンピュータ言語の反復ループという概念に由来する。C・Unixプログラマの間ではあまり一般的でないcdr "
"down(\\ :ref:`cdr`\\ の項を参照)と比較せよ。ITSハッカーはかつて、MIDAS "
"PDP-10アセンブラのある難解な疑似命令にちなんでIRP overと言っていた(同じIRP命令は今ではMicrosoftのアセンブラにも見られる)。"
